About 70 firefighters have tackled an overnight blaze at a former primary school in Renfrewshire. Blaze at former St James Primary School in Renfrew About 70 firefighters have tackled an overnight blaze at a former primary school in Renfrewshire.
Crews were called to the former St James Primary School, near Porterfield Road, Renfrew, at about 20:30 on Sunday.
They arrived to find a well-developed fire in the single-storey building.
The crews used large volume water jets and aerial appliances to fight the fire. There were no reports of anyone being injured.
 